i1 and current i2--

00:03:01.850 --> 00:03:05.540
is equal to the product of the
two currents, divided by r,

00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:09.620
times l-- the length
of the wires--

00:03:09.620 --> 00:03:12.098
times mu 0 over 2 pi.

00:03:12.098 --> 00:03:13.640
So this is fantastic,
because now you

00:03:13.640 --> 00:03:15.770
can calculate the
speed of light by just

00:03:15.770 --> 00:03:17.690
measuring the forces
between charges

00:03:17.690 --> 00:03:21.900
and current in wire's centers.

00:03:21.900 --> 00:03:24.870
